<br>
We know that you know that we all like to whine a little in the Bard board, when we feel that we have been slighted, or short changed. However the time has come for us to ask ... politely ... that you take a little trip to the nearest local and relieve yourself of any tensions, so we can, then, ask you a few requests, that we thought might give some of your folks a few more ideas of what we might like to see in this class. We understand that you want to kill the Bard, and that in the next generation of Eq, it won't even be close to the best class any game has ever invented, but what the heck ... kill the best class and kill a game ... hopefully not!<br>
<br>
You know well, that in this board here, we do not get along and could not agree on how many angels on a pin can give head, or how much of a head of foam is really needed on a glass for proper taste ... and that togetherness here is a new joke, since some folks are so eager on going to work for you ... hey ... one can dream, right? ... and can not look past their PL'ing and easy levelling compared to some of us that had to go through Kunark days of not being needed, or wanted in any groups ... everyone else did it better. But we thought, that since the Monk Boards were so successful in asking you for Lull, that we should, likewise, ask you for a small version of Feign Death ... after all, fair is fair ... and Monks do a heck of a lot more damage than a Bard does, and even gets the benefit of the over the cap Haste, when group'd together ... <br>
<br>
We would like to ask for AE songs, it seems, but personally, I would lilke a song with the same attributes for rresists, let's say, that is NOT an AE song ... so we can adjust and improve our raid performances ... ohh, yeah, I know you know we pull for them anyway, but in the fighting stuff, I don't see why I, or any Bard should have to carry a whole raid on our shoulders with one song ... I would like to 6 box my own group ... gotta keep up with the Gimp'ism all around, and provide my own resists, so I can stay in one piece and not have to deal with morons that do not have any resist items, and are not interested in any, because they think the Bard should kiss and save their buns from a tan, and toast!<br>
<br>
So, all in all, I think we are the best class in any game ... the numbers show it, and many a mob at the high level can not be done without us ... that's an honor ... but it would be nice if for once I can FD, and laugh at all the folks going LD while feared, like many Monks do. I always thought that whinning was not necessary and that good folkls would read the stuff and discuss it ... or as Alan Shore asked ... Jimmy ... do you think you could separate your personal feelings from your legal work? ... no, I suppose I couldn't ... and the poor guy could not see that he just ten arrows through his foot ... I like to think that most of us Bards here are much more intelligent and are able of discussing this topic with you, even over a couple of beers ... head not withstanding!<br>
<br>
Moshkiae Soulwriter <p>Moshkiae Soulwriter, the non role playing Bard / Mo'riae Soulmender - Cleric</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub147.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=moshkiae>Moshkiae</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0> at: 3/31/04 11:31 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub147.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=twingereborn>Twinge Reborn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#330000>(3/31/04 2:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19225.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: a dear brenlo message... what would you say?</span><hr size=1> Dear Brenlo, <br>
