<br>
I find the idea of modifiying one group member as a &quot;step up&quot; replacement very intresting. <br>
<br>
Let me expand on it if you don't mind.<br>
<br>
Add a set of AAs that are all on the same timers (similar to discs) with a 19 minute recast and 20 minute duration that have the following effect to a targetted member (and not self targetable):<br>
1. provide overhaste 50% to any class except rogue.<br>
2. provide +5% mitigation +10% avoidance to any class except warrior.<br>
3. provide +15% mitigation +20% avoidance to any class except warrior/sk/pally.<br>
4. provide +30% healing to any class except cleric.<br>
5. provide +50% healing to any class except cleric/druid<br>
6. provide 50% DD focus to any class except wizard/mage.<br>
7. etc...<br>
<br>
Don't take the numbers to heart... I didn't really think about the effect of them.  They are just sample values.  This is just a demo concept of a Ellessar idea.<br>
<br>
Of course, implementing the above is almost enough work to create a completely new class. <p><script type='text/javascript' >
