<br>
Having AE 'overhaste' wouldn't be nearly as overpowering as it sounds--I think you'd find that it would bring the melee back into the game a bit in terms of DPS.  It would also address some of the problems that others (*cough* monks) are currently concerned with.<br>
<br>
I do like some of Ellessar's ideas--my biggest fear would be the massive change (AKA massive breaking while they implement it!) to the class.  I think having Focus Effects affect bards will be somewhere in the natural progression of the class as they run out of ways to improve us.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub147.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kereven>kereven</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Minstrel</span><br>  Posts: 242<br> <font color=#330000>(3/31/04 4:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19225.topic&index=27>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: a dear brenlo message... what would you say?</span><hr size=1> After spending the last few days trying to explain why monks aren't balanced based on overhaste over on their boards, and why overhaste doesn't necessarily HAVE to be farmed out to other classes, I'm dead set against an AOE version.<br>
<br>
If we don't need to sing resists and we're not in a main tank group, then our DPS contribution is through overhaste. This is carefully balanced so that overhasting 5 of the same class represents the addition of 75% of that class - plus our own DPS.  Making an AOE version would screw that balance up and take away bard stackability.  <br>
<br>
If melee need help, then why not upgrade melee directly, instead of increasing the amount we buff them by?  Especially since most of our later overhastes also buff casters, so we're either in a caster group singing a much-reduced-in-effestivness Riz, or we're  AOE buffing casters AND melee and balance doesn't change. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub147.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=worry07>worry07</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Minstrel</span><br>  Posts: 295<br> <font color=#330000>(3/31/04 4:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19225.topic&index=28>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: a dear brenlo message... what would you say?</span><hr size=1> i love the fact that mosh saw a need to edit his post, heheh <p><br>
