<br>
One of the reasons that I'm a proponent of the AE Overhaste is based on my interpretation from Lucy of the current songs (using Call of the Muse here):<br>
<br>
3:  Limit: Effect(Hitpoints allowed) <br>
4:  Limit: Max Level(65) <br>
5:  Limit: Spell Type(Detrimental only) <br>
6:  Limit: Target(AE PC v1 excluded) <br>
7:  Limit: Target(PB AE excluded) <br>
8:  Limit: Target(Targeted AE excluded) <br>
9:  Limit: Target(Uber Giants excluded) <br>
10:  Limit: Target(Uber Dragons excluded) <br>
<br>
I may be totally wrong in how I'm reading that, but it seems to me that slots 9 and 10 roughly translate to 'Boss Mobs'.  If that's the case, then certainly on the Named/Boss/Loot/whatever mobs it would help the melee more.  <br>
<br>
I'm also not clear on what slot 4 refers to--I believe it's max level of a mob that this song will help do extra damage on.  Most of the stuff that we're up against at the high end of GoD is over level 65.  I think there are only three mobs in Uqua that are actually under level 65...<br>
<br>
So if I have interpreted Lucy correctly, casters really wouldn't gain very much on an AE version of this in the end game.  It would be worthwhile to lower slot 4 to 60 or so if it was a problem in lower-end encounters.<br>
<br>
I don't want to ignore your point about upgrading melee directly, but I would like to stick to 'What do bards need?' or 'What would make bards more desirable?'.  I think an AE version of this song would be a nice addition to the raid. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub147.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kereven>kereven</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Minstrel</span><br>  Posts: 243<br> <font color=#330000>(3/31/04 5:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19225.topic&index=30>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: a dear brenlo message... what would you say?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>One of the reasons that I'm a proponent of the AE Overhaste is based on my interpretation from Lucy of the current songs (using Call of the Muse here):<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
