<br>
Every class in the game has a compelling reason to include a couple of them on a raid.  Having a bard on a raid is almost mandatory.  Just like having a shaman on a raid is mandatory.  The question that needs to be asked <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>'Given a couple bards already on the raid, how do you make <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">additional</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> bards more desirable?'</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->  (this applies to all classes.)<br>
 <br>
An AE song would be a huge NERF.  It would dramatically reduce the effectiveness of the additional bards on a raid. (Even if the AE song was a lower haste, it still reduces the marginal contribution that adding a bard makes.)<br>
<br>
----<br>
and on a different note... plate armor.  Its a curse.  Too many classes (and populous ones) compete for it; equipment does too little for bards to begin with.  In terms of gear, equipping bards is a nightmare.<br>
<br>
Breaking out plate into a light and heavy version would be a major win for bards.  Don't need to change the stats or anything.  Just break up armor drops into 5 categories, rather than 4.  <br>
