<br>
I also believe that Sony, rather misguidedly, use poor itemisation of some classes, bard in particular, for balancing. The obscurity of elemental instruments is, I believe a symptom of this, and possibly perceived as a karma effect to counteract the general utility of bards. Perhaps the comparative rarity of plate is intentional, and done for reasons of balance? I'm not saying I think it's the right thing to do, but that might be the logic. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showMessageRange?topicID=19225.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a> <b>2</b> <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showMessageRange?topicID=19225.topic&start=41&stop=57>3</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showPrevMessage?topicID=19225.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showNextMessage?topicID=19225.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19225.topic&index=40><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/traditional/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.emailToFriend?topicID=19225.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.threadControl?topicID=19225.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/traditional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=19225.topic><img src=http://www.ezboa